---
title: Marquee Text
description: Infinite scrolling text using CSS `translateX` and `@keyframes` — the modern replacement for `<marquee>`.
slug: marquee-text
cssFile: marquee-text.css
explanation: "The seamless loop requires the content to be duplicated inside `.marquee-inner`. The animation moves from `translateX(0)` to `translateX(-50%)` — at the halfway point, the second copy has slid into where the first started, making the jump back to 0 invisible. `animation-play-state: paused` on `:hover` stops the scroll so users can read the content."
---
{% extends "example.njk" %}
{% block demo %}
<div class="demo-marquee-text">
	<div class="marquee-track">
		<div class="marquee-inner">
			<span class="marquee-item">Pure CSS</span>
			<span class="marquee-item">Zero JavaScript</span>
			<span class="marquee-item marquee-item-accent">No Dependencies</span>
